This paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics, specifically the study of planar 3-connected graphs and their spanning trees. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), followed by cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves some graph theoretic concepts such as duals and degrees, which could place it in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
